he basis of where and how they allow phrasal structure, rather than on the basis of a yes-no answer to the question of constituency. The analysis also shows that a determiner slot can be identified in about half of the languages, even though they generally lack 'classic' determiner features like obligatory use in particular contexts or a restriction to one determiner per NP. Special attention is given to elements, which can be used both inside and beyond determiner slots, demonstrating how part of speech and functional structure do not always align. The book is of interest to researchers documenting Australian languages, as well as to typologists and theorists.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aAustralian languagesxSemantics. 0aAustralian languageszAustralia. 4aAustralische Sprache. 4aNominalphrase. 4aSprachtypologie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aAustralia.  aLinguistic Typology.  aNoun Phrase.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Frontlist 2020z978311074316608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019 Englishz978311061030708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019z9783110606287oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015128720 cprintz978150151780840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150151293340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501512933423Coveruhttps://www.